description: For sale: $538,000. Best location in Lake Elmo! Custom blt home on wooded 10 acres w/pond. For sale: $534,570. Create the lifestyle of your dreams in the bold, effortless luxury of the Kaiden floorplan. This open-concept home features 3,256 square feet with 4 bedrooms, 3 bathrooms and an insulated 3-car garage. Main-level living means you'll get to enjoy a main-level owner's suite and laundry room.The kitchen is every chef's dream with stainless steel appliances including a gas range, quartz countertops, a large center island, an undermount sink, gorgeous tile backsplash, under-cabinet lighting and a corner pantry with glass door. The family room has pan-vault ceiling, gas burning fireplace with cultured stone surround, and a wrapped box mantel flanked by two base cabinets and six additional LED lights. Retire to the elegance of the owner's suite that features an amazing bathroom with a tile surround walk-in shower and a semi-frameless shower door, separate water closet with a pocket door, quartz countertop, dual sinks, linen cabinet, and generous size walk-in closet. Conveniently located just steps away from the owner's suite is the laundry room with a folding table and a soaking sink with cabinet above for extra storage. The lower level has a finished recreation room with another gas burning fireplace, the fourth bedroom, a full-size bathroom, and plenty of space for a future exercise room and a flex room. Schedule a private tour with a New Home Consultant and view your new home today!

description: Recently sold: $919,750. Built by DeWitt Homes, this mansion of a home spans over 7,000 finished square feet, yet is very welcoming and easy to live in with a floor plan that flows from one room to the next and convenient main level living.  As you enter to a grand, two-story foyer, the sight lines reflect a luxury lifestyle with an open catwalk above and walls of floor-to-ceiling windows in the great room providing incredible views and phenomenal light, in addition to the two-story stacked stone fireplace flanked by built-ins.  The entire main level feels fresh and new with white painted trim, doors, windows and cabinets that you'll find in rooms like the spacious den with beautiful bay windows and a wall of built-ins, formal dining room with a dazzling chandelier, and butler's pantry that leads to the striking gourmet kitchen.  A distinguished center island is large enough to comfortably sit five and proportioned on scale with the rest of the room that features new lighting and mosaic backsplash, casual dining, endless white cabinetry, a walk-in pantry and built-in planning center, plus access to a three-season porch and grill deck.  The main level also offers the private Owner's suite lending serene views through its oversized windows, as well as marvelously updated laundry and powder rooms and a mudroom with handy built-in lockers and second staircase to the upper level.  The open catwalk connects four bedrooms that offer walk-in closets and two completely updated, stunning baths, including a full Jack & Jill with private vanities and a ¾ walk-thru en suite with tile surround shower.  The sixth bedroom can be found in the walkout basement, along with two more updated baths and wonderful space made to entertain with an impressive built-in entertainment center and gas fireplace in the family room, billiards room and full wet bar with new flooring and backsplash, granite counters and a full-size refrigerator and dishwasher.  Three separate walkouts then lead to the large saltwater pool surrounded by a stamped concrete patio in the sweeping backyard.  As the owners share, "It feels like a private, luxury home in the country; it's the place where friends and family want to visit for holidays and social gatherings."

description: Recently sold: $274,900. Beautiful Brookside Estates Norcutt-built one level at a comfortable price! description: Recently sold: $425,000. This executive 1-level, with walkout, is situated in the popular Stonebrook community. Most everything has been updated with high-end upgrades throughout. Has a very open concept and easy flow to it and includes 33 panes of glass for lots of natural light. Red Oak floors on main level are absolutely beautiful. This was a 3-bedroom plan but closet in office was converted for use in mud room, can be converted back to bedroom. The gorgeous pond views and location of this unit are spectacular.

Recently sold: $289,900. Welcome to 9300 Hillingdon Road! This lovely home will impress you the moment you step through the front door with its vaulted ceilings, sunlit filled rooms, gleaming hardwood floors, and spacious backyard.

The informal dining room welcomes you in and will be an ideal place to host family and friends for holiday celebrations and intimate gatherings alike. Floor to ceiling windows look out to the deck and allow light to fill this room all year long. The open layout between this space and kitchen means socializing with your guests is fun and easy.

The home?s kitchen boasts beautiful silestone counters, shaker cabinets, and stone-tiled backsplashes. Pull up to the breakfast bar for weekend pancakes!  Whipping up your favorite recipes here is a breeze thanks to ample counter space and abundant cabinetry to house your cookware.

Travel to the upper level to find the living room which features soft, neutral carpeting, wonderful views across the backyard, and a vaulted ceiling. What a great place for movie nights or to relax with your newest book as you soak up the natural daylight.

Two bedrooms sit on this level as well, one of which is the owner?s suite with a walk-in closet and a walk-through bathroom ensuite featuring craftsman tile.


A lower level lays claim to a brick-faced, gas fireplace; what an ideal spot to sit on a cool morning with a cup of coffee in front of the fire. This room is spacious and flooded with daylight thanks to windows lining the wall offering views out to the backyard. Along the hallway you will find the third bedroom, a ¾ bathroom, and great storage. 

An attached two car garage will keep your cars and toys free from the elements year round. Soak up the warm sunshine on the deck or host barbecues with friends on long Fall days! A fully fenced backyard will allow your four-legged friends to explore worry free. Let your green thumb shape the yard thanks to ample sunlight. Store tools with ease in the shed!

Stepping out your front door, miles of walking, biking, and running trails can be found just minutes away around Colby Lake. description: Recently sold: $717,000. Custom-built by Kootenia Homes in the highly desired neighborhood of Wedgewood Heights, this sophisticated home boasts a contemporary design and impressive details that make it few and far between.  Great for everyday living, rooms flow from one to another, and tons of living space make entertaining a breeze.  Starting in the two-story great room, you'll love the loads of natural daylight that pour in from its wall of windows, along with its stunning, floor-to-ceiling fireplace and private views of your treed backyard.  And in the spacious kitchen, you'll appreciate an abundance of white enamel cabinetry and Corian counter space, along with high-end appliances, a wine fridge, walk-in pantry and large center island with granite countertop.  In addition, a cozy sunroom with a built-in window seat is the perfect retreat to enjoy your morning coffee and views of the outdoor pool in the fenced-in backyard, and an informal dining space, as well as seating at the island provide extra dining options, in addition to the elegant formal dining room.  To finish off the main level is a functional office with built-in workstations, desirable laundry room and mudroom with built-ins.  On the upper level, you'll find another built-in dual workstation in the open loft and three spacious bedrooms with walk-in closets and accommodating en suite baths, including the expansive master suite that features a vaulted tray ceiling, electric fireplace and oversized en suite with a two-person walk-in shower, whirlpool tub and huge dressing room.  The fourth bedroom can then be found in the lower level that features tons of lookout windows, along with a family room and recreation space, huge wet bar with in-floor heat, wine cellar, relaxing hot tub room, exercise room and ¾ bath.  Located on a private cul-de-sac lot, surrounded by mature trees and open space, this home is a sanctuary you'll delight in year-round.

description: Recently sold: $399,000. Beautiful 4BR/3BA home in fantastic location! Completely remodeled by Ispiri in 2015 with gorgeous new baths, impressive chef's kitchen with high-end appliances and tons of cabinetry, new lighting, and engineered hardwood floors throughout main level. 3 bedrooms conveniently located on upper level, plus full bath and private ¾ bath in master suite. Outside, enjoy updated landscaping and tons of perennials, large two-level deck, and fire pit in treed backyard that borders parkland with direct access to a trail system and walking distance to Ojibway Park.

Recently sold: $216,000. Welcome to this well maintained townhome nestled in the heart of Woodbury!  This home sits at the end of a cul-de-sac and features wooded views out the back.  A private, well appointed courtyard greets you upon arrival, complete with fountain, custom outdoor fireplace, and artificial turf.  A light, bright kitchen features updated appliances and tile flooring.  Living/Dining room features crown molding, laminate flooring, and access to a spacious back deck.  Cozy up to the wood burning fireplace on a cold winter evening.  Upstairs features a spacious loft and two bedrooms, including a master bedroom with walk through bath.  Walkout lower level features a kitchenette and a large 3rd bedroom, perfect for a potential In-law suite.  Spacious 2 car garage and expansive asphalt driveway allows for plenty off parking.  All of this just seconds from all that Woodbury has to offer.  Schedule your showing today!

description: Recently sold: $549,000. A classic beauty built with craftsmanship on a perfect lot that can?t be found in today?s new construction. Lovingly cared for and thoughtfully updated, this home has endless charm and beautiful surroundings set on a private corner lot backing up to the Wedgewood Heights parks and walking trails. A side-loading garage gives the home striking curb appeal and allows for a hospitable covered front porch that introduces white pillars connected by architectural curved arches. Textural cedar shakes painted in a greige hue are paired with stone accents on the front exterior, while wine-colored shutters frame the windows and pull color from the stone accents. Add a curved concrete sidewalk, extensive landscaping, Hardie® board siding on the sides and back of the home, large paver patio with built-in fire pit, and a deck stained to coordinate with the shutters and roof of the home, and you have created a pleasing color story and graceful transition to the interior spaces. Built by Kootenia homes, it shows all of the characteristics of the master craftsmanship this builder is known for. You first notice it as you enter to a generous foyer boasting with thick creamy-colored and curved millwork that frames the openings to the formal dining and sitting rooms. Bay windows with wide plank plantation shutters, decorative pillars and staircase spindles are painted in the same creamy white, blending successfully with the oak hardwood flooring and solid maple cabinets and millwork stained in a rich pecan shade throughout the main level. A gas fireplace in the family room is surrounded with floor-to-ceiling large-scale river rock stones, embellished with a maple mantel and flanked with built-in maple cabinets that house the TV and other electronics. The professional grade kitchen features Capella granite, a top-of-the-line selection that unfolds a loose textual pattern that is calming and easy on the eyes. It marries with white tile back splash and the decorative inlay above the gas cooktop with griddle and chef?s grade stainless steel range hood. You will also love the sunny bayed casual dining area that walks out to the deck and private backyard overlooking a walking path and green belt. Three bedrooms can be found on the upper level, one of which is the owner?s suite that showcases a vaulted ceiling with dentil crown moulding and striking hardwood floors centered by a carpet inlay, while honest materials set the framework for the remodeled owner?s en suite. Another well-chosen granite tops the shaker style white cabinets, and glass tile accents, wall sconces, a frameless glass shower door, and neutral-colored timeless and durable tile on the floor, shower and tub surround complete the space. The recently completed lower level offers plenty of additional living space with a large family room that features a gas fireplace with stone surround and built-in bar that includes a beverage fridge and computer work station, an office, 4th bedroom, 3/4 bath and wine cellar. Undeniably cozy and in a wonderful location, you will want to call this one home for a lifetime.

description: Recently sold: $559,000. Located on the 9th fairway of Prestwick Golf Club in the prestigious Wedgewood Estates neighborhood, this executive home offers a unique layout and twelve rooms with southern exposure windows that offer fantastic views of the golf course.  Enjoy an open floor plan through the kitchen, dining and great room, where you can cozy up to a wood burning fireplace or take in the serene views from the nearby four-season porch or huge deck in back.  Formal living and dining rooms provide that extra needed space for entertaining, while an office is located off the foyer and a main level laundry room makes for a convenient amenity.  A grand, open staircase then leads to the upper level, where there are four bedrooms and two full bathrooms, including the spacious master suite that includes a sitting nook with some of the best views in the house, large en suite with a separate shower and whirlpool tub, and walk-in closet.  A fifth bedroom can be found in the lower level, along with the family room that offers a wet bar and walkout to a sports court in the backyard, as well as a huge recreation room with plenty of room for fun and games.  With tremendous potential and all the space you could ask for, put your personal touches on a home you would be proud to call your own.

description: Recently sold: $635,000. Situated on an exceedingly private lot at the end of a cul-de-sac, this exquisite home dazzles with details and finishes that are sure to impress even the fussiest of buyers.  As you make your way up a long driveway, you?ll find it is nestled amongst mature trees and landscaping, and the curb appeal is warm and inviting with a cozy front porch adorned with stone accented steps and pillars.  Inside, a conveniently located office sits off the foyer through a set of glass French doors, offering walls of beautiful built-ins and a view into the finest of living rooms.  Walls of windows allow loads of natural daylight to pour in this space, while an elegant chandelier, wall sconces, and a gas fireplace surrounded by a lovely white mantle will make your eyes dance.  From here, a formal dining room with a convenient built-in buffet sits around the corner, next to the wonderfully open kitchen and great room area.  Gorgeous cherry cabinetry fills the kitchen, and the entire back wall of the great room has likewise been designed with cherry built-ins, window seats and mantle surrounding another wonderful gas fireplace.  In addition, the informal dining space is surrounded by windows, lending private, serene views of the pond and woods beyond the backyard and patio door access to the deck.  Highly desired on the upper level are four bedrooms and two full baths, including the luxurious master suite with its relaxing sitting nook, huge walk-in closet and tastefully updated en suite with soaking tub, double vanities and large tile surround shower with a bench and dual shower heads.  Finally, the impressive lower level has been finished into a space perfect for entertaining, starting with a family room that features a soft carpet inlay and cherry built-in entertainment center and fireplace surround, as well as ample recreation space and a stately wet bar with wine cellar.  There is also a study with built-in workstations that conveniently converts to a fifth bedroom with its handy Murphy bed, an exercise room, and a useful hobby/craft room.  Feel at ease in a home that has been continuously updated, well-maintained and lovingly cared for since the day it was built.

description: Recently sold: $630,000. Located on a private 1-acre lot on Prestwick Golf Club, this stunning home built by Derrick Custom Homes is a rare find in the highly desired neighborhood of Wedgewood Heights.  With an open floor plan and all living facilities on the main level, you can enjoy easy living and an abundance of space to entertain.  A formal dining room with a built-in buffet and display cabinets sits off the main entrance foyer, while another pass-through buffet between the kitchen and living room are favorable conveniences for hosting holidays and dinner parties.  The spacious and vaulted kitchen also features a large center island with seating, plenty of custom cabinetry, a pantry and handy workstation.  In addition, this space runs into a cozy sunroom that offers a custom built-in entertainment center and serene views of the wooded backyard, while also giving access to an especially private, 3-season screened porch encased in wood paneling.  Off the kitchen is easy access from the garage, as well as the laundry/mudroom with a separate side entrance door.  To complete this level is the large Owner?s suite, where you?ll be pleased to find numerous windows and more private views of the backyard, as well as a gas fireplace with room for a reading nook.  And in the sizable en suite is a walk-in closet, in-floor heat, whirlpool tub and walk-in tiled shower.  Three additional bedrooms and two baths can be found in the walkout lower level that also provides extra living space in the family room, featuring a corner stone surround fireplace and custom built-in entertainment center, and a full wet bar, perfect for entertaining and accommodating guests.  One of the bedrooms is currently being utilized as an exercise room, with a steam shower and built-in lockers in the ¾ bath around the corner, and a thoughtfully-placed office with an impressive built-in workstation and cedar walk-in closet sits far from distraction.  Just as favorable is the fantastic outdoor space with a stone paver patio overlooking a lovely koi pond and 2-tier waterfall; and mature landscaping and trees ensure all the privacy you could ask for.  With all of these exceptional amenities and more, this beautiful property is one you will look forward to coming home to.
